TableContextTimeStampBeforeTable: {8335=In 2006, ABS launched ABS Sexation® sex-sorted semen providing producers the opportunity to “GROW from within”. Just a year later, ABS launched the DURAbulls brand in conjunction with the GMS durability formula to promote healthy cows built to last., 8940=Progeny testing has always been a priority at ABS, and has been the foundation of the ABS Beef program since the late 1960’s. In 1995, American Breeders Service was renamed to ABS Global, Inc. to fully recognize the company’s dedication to beef and dairy producers around the globe. In 1999, ABS was purchased by its current parent company, Genus, plc, who plays a key role in the world’s agricultural economy. Genus creates advances in animal breeding through naturally applied biotechnology, helping farmers and food producers across the world to improve quality and increase output., 9502=ABS was proud to launch the Genetic Management System® in 1968, developed to optimize sire selection and avoid inbreeding through computerized mating. By 1985, over 500,000 dairy cows in the United States were mated through the GMS program., 6929=Headquartered in DeForest, Wisconsin, ABS Global is the world-leading provider of bovine genetics, reproduction services, technologies and uddercare products. Marketing in more than 80 countries around the globe, ABS has been at the forefront of animal genetics and technology since its founding in 1941. ABS Global is a division of Genus plc., 9947=Founded in 1941 by J.R. “Rock” Prentice as American Breeders Service, ABS has influenced the entire artificial insemination industry through its business, philosophy, dedicated staff and technical innovation. Just 12 years after its foundation, ABS was the first to utilize liquid nitrogen technology to freeze bovine semen and has been on the cutting edge of technology and meeting the world’s production demands ever since., 9238=Dedicated to looking out for all aspects of the dairy customer, ABS launched the Quality Milk System® in 1990 and added the Valiant® product line in 1998, which still focuses on producer’s milk quality and utilizing the best products in the business for maximum results., 6566=06.13.2011}
